From: Sujeet Kumar <sujeet.kumar@inventum.net>
Date: Mon, 09 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] hostapd: fix ubus ban timer units in hostapd_bss_ban_client

eloop_register_timeout() takes (seconds, microseconds, ...) but the
original code passed ban_time in the microseconds argument:

  eloop_register_timeout(0, time * 1000, hostapd_bss_del_ban, ...);

With ban_time=30 this set a 30ms timer instead of 30 seconds, causing
the ban to expire almost immediately and allowing clients to reconnect
right after being kicked.

Fix by passing ban_time as seconds in the first argument:

  eloop_register_timeout(time, 0, hostapd_bss_del_ban, ...);

Signed-off-by: Sujeet Kumar <sujeet.kumar@inventum.net>
---
 .../hostapd/src/src/ap/ubus.c                 | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/package/network/services/hostapd/src/src/ap/ubus.c b/package/network/services/hostapd/src/src/ap/ubus.c
--- a/package/network/services/hostapd/src/src/ap/ubus.c
+++ b/package/network/services/hostapd/src/src/ap/ubus.c
@@ -147,7 +147,7 @@ hostapd_bss_ban_client(struct hostapd_data *hapd, u8 *addr, int time)
 	} else {
 		eloop_cancel_timeout(hostapd_bss_del_ban, ban, hapd);
 		if (!time) {
 			hostapd_bss_del_ban(ban, hapd);
 			return;
 		}
 	}
-	eloop_register_timeout(0, time * 1000, hostapd_bss_del_ban, ban, hapd);
+	eloop_register_timeout(time, 0, hostapd_bss_del_ban, ban, hapd);
 }
